ng": "1.0", "difficulty": "3.0", "course_code": "ENGL111W", "date": "Jun 24th, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "No", "Grade": "A+", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "The course itself is interesting . But the attitude of this instructor is unacceptable . Never take courses with this woman , ever, again !!!!!", "helpful": "0", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": []}, {"rating": "3.0", "difficulty": "3.0", "course_code": "ENGL111W", "date": "Jun 19th, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Not Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Grade": "B+", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "I enjoyed the lectures and the reading material, this course was very sci-fi heavy (which I was happy about!) I don't understand all the negative comments, I thought this class was fine. I didn't love my TA or tutorial (a lot of students there who clearly didn't care to be there and put little to no effort in.) The class itself was enjoyable!", "helpful": "0", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": ["Get ready to read"]}, {"rating": "1.0", "difficulty": "5.0", "course_code": "ENGL349", "date": "Apr 30th, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "No", "Grade": "C-", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "Be an English teacher yet keep misusing the word \"literally\" just bcuz she thinks she sounds cool when saying it. Hilarious !!!! Plus her attitude toward students is unacceptable too!Never smile once!!!", "helpful": "1", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": []}, {"rating": "1.0", "difficulty": "5.0", "course_code": "ENGL111W", "date": "Apr 23rd, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "No", "Grade": "C-", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "terrible!", "helpful": "0", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": ["Lecture heavy", "Tough grader"]}, {"rating": "5.0", "difficulty": "2.0", "course_code": "ENGL111W", "date": "Apr 22nd, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Textbook": "No"}, "review_msg": "Absolutely fantastic, very interesting, presents an extremely nuanced look at all the texts read. If I had one complaint it would be the first \"in-class\" paper, which she expected us to be prepared for without telling us the questions we were preparing for. However, she took feedback and the remaining papers were much better/smoother.", "helpful": "0", "not_helpful": "2", "tags": ["Get ready to read", "Amazing lectures"]}, {"rating": "1.0", "difficulty": "5.0", "course_code": "ENGL112", "date": "Apr 22nd, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "No", "Grade": "Drop/Withdrawal", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "i dropped this course because she is just so disrespectful toward students .", "helpful": "2", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": []}, {"rating": "1.0", "difficulty": "5.0", "course_code": "ENGL115", "date": "Apr 20th, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "No", "Grade": "Drop/Withdrawal", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "bad teacher , terrible work ethics", "helpful": "1", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": []}, {"rating": "5.0", "difficulty": "4.0", "course_code": "ENGL111W", "date": "Mar 28th, 2020", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "Alison's lectures are truly inspiring and vigorous. The ideas she presents seep into your head and have the capacity to impact you on a much deeper level. Definitely a life-changing experience, look at what you gain beyond just the grades. Not saying it's a hard course, but expect to really explore your ideas and presenting them in your essays :)", "helpful": "0", "not_helpful": "1", "tags": ["Inspirational"]}, {"rating": "1.0", "difficulty": "5.0", "course_code": "ENG111W", "date": "Feb 27th, 2020", "metadata": {"Would Take Again": "No", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "There was very little in-depth discussion on the books. The lectures addressed more historical context which is supposed to help my understanding of the book, but I found it useless and not helpful at all. I found it unfair that our marks were based mainly on the in-class writing assignments for which we had only 40 minutes to write full essays.", "helpful": "0", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": []}, {"rating": "5.0", "difficulty": "3.0", "course_code": "ENGL115", "date": "May 18th, 2019", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Grade": "B", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "I would recommend her", "helpful": "1", "not_helpful": "0", "tags": []}, {"rating": "5.0", "difficulty": "4.0", "course_code": "ENGL112", "date": "Jan 23rd, 2018", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "One of the best english teachers in my entire life!!! Her teaching is pretty attractive and never get boring. She is always kind to any students who ask question even in not fluent english. It's my pleasure being her student in this institute.", "helpful": "4", "not_helpful": "4", "tags": ["Gives good feedback", "Respected", "Get ready to read"]}, {"rating": "4.0", "difficulty": "4.0", "course_code": "ENGL349", "date": "Sep 19th, 2017", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Would Take Again": "Yes", "Grade": "B", "Textbook": "No"}, "review_msg": "great teacher", "helpful": "2", "not_helpful": "4", "tags": ["Respected"]}, {"rating": "1.5", "difficulty": "4.0", "course_code": "ENGL349", "date": "Apr 27th, 2016", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Grade": "Drop/Withdrawal", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "I found the lectures pretty boring, however you can tell she's very passionate about photography.  I felt it had little to do with what we were reading and just an add on. The final essay was incredibly hard to understand in terms of what she wanted. I didn't find her helpful, however she seemed to care, a little? The topic itself was interesting.", "helpful": "7", "not_helpful": "2", "tags": []}, {"rating": "4.5", "difficulty": "3.0", "course_code": "ENGL349", "date": "Jul 9th, 2015", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Textbook": "Yes"}, "review_msg": "Tough course (lots of reading, fair marker) but professor made it manageable.", "helpful": "2", "not_helpful": "1", "tags": []}, {"rating": "4.0", "difficulty": "3.0", "course_code": "ENGL349", "date": "Jul 1st, 2015", "metadata": {"For Credit": "Yes", "Attendance": "Mandatory", "Grade": "B", "Textbook": "No"}, "review_msg": "It was an okay course. Focused on the Harlem Renaissance, its literature, and a surprising amount on photography. Quite a lot of reading, about as many assignments as a 400-level course, and a final to boot. Lectures were sort of dry because it was just going through slides relating to the texts and a lot of the essays on photography were tedious.", "helpful": "2", "not_helpful": "2", "tags": []}]}